column5: My MS Internet Explorer keeps crashing about every 5 minutes or so, I downloaded Google Chrome web browser yesterday, it seems to work ok. It's a little different but for basic surfing it works pretty good.  Seems to have trouble with interactive mapping stuff, though.

I try to stay with the tried and true until such time that something proves itself to be better. I learned early in life that being a pioneer is as frustrating as it is expensive and time consuming. I'm using Firefox for the time being and it serves my purpose well.
The only plus to Chrome is the "ctrl+shift+n" function. MOST guys will appreciate this!
